About Me

Hi, I'm Linh Klatt. After spending five years as a stay-at-home mom, I made the decision to return to school and pursue my passion for software engineering. I've always had a fascination with computers and technology, enjoying the process of troubleshooting, hands-on work, problem-solving, and finding solutions. Currently, I'm attending a Coding Bootcamp at UCSD while also working towards completing my AA degree. My ultimate goal is to transfer to either UCSD or USUSM. Currently, I'm working as a project team leader at a global company that specializes in innovative distribution, fulfillment, and reverse logistics services for the wireless communications industry.
